        "timestamp": "2018-03-08 03:23:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe build logs are flooded with warnings due to incorrectly formatted test code. In a recent jenkins log there were 25,577 matches to \"warning: Line contains a tab character.\", and 9,766 matches for \"warning: 'method def' child have incorrect indentation\". This patch should reduce logs by my than ~34,000 lines on each build.\n\nExamples of warnings that this patch fixes:\n/w/workspace/so-master-merge-profile-java/bpmn/MSOInfrastructureBPMN/src/test/java/org/openecomp/mso/bpmn/infrastructure/CreateVfModuleVolumeInfraV1Test.java:177:1: warning: Line contains a tab character.\n/w/workspace/so-master-merge-profile-java/bpmn/MSOInfrastructureBPMN/src/test/java/org/openecomp/mso/bpmn/infrastructure/CreateVfModuleVolumeInfraV1Test.java:178: warning: 'method def' child have incorrect indentation level 16, expected level should be 8.\n\nSearch an example log in Jenkins for \"warning: Line contains a tab character\" here: https://logs.onap.org/production/vex-yul-ecomp-jenkins-1/so-master-verify-profile-java/1024/console.log.gz",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
